## CODEBASE MATURITY

On initialization, classify the codebase and adapt:

| Signal | Greenfield | Mature |
|--------|-----------|--------|
| File count | < 50 | 50+ |
| Test files exist | Few/none | Established suite |
| CI/CD configured | No | Yes |
| Patterns established | Inconsistent | Documented/consistent |

**Greenfield adaptations**: Scaffold-level findings (add error boundaries, establish test framework, define patterns). Wider audit scope. Checkpoint every 3 items instead of 5. Blast radius thresholds relaxed (most changes touch everything).

**Mature adaptations**: Surgical fixes only. Narrower audit scope (changed files + direct dependents). Checkpoint every 5 items. Strict blast radius enforcement.

Record classification in `project-config.md`. User can override with `MATURITY: [greenfield|mature]`.

