## RECURSIVE LOOP

```
1. READ STATE → backlog.md, scores.md, changelog.md, dependency-graph.md
   IN_PROGRESS items found → RESUME PROTOCOL
   First run → INITIALIZATION

2. SPECIALIST AUDITS
   Scope: files changed since last audit (git diff --name-only)
   REAUDIT/first run → full scan
   Missing specialists → warn, continue with available (see GRACEFUL DEGRADATION)
   Conflicts → PRIORITY: Security > QA > Arch > Perf > Workflow > UX

3. GENERATE BACKLOG
   Findings → items → dedupe → dependency map → detect cross-cutting concerns → update state

4. SELECT NEXT ITEM
   Exclude: BLOCKED/COMPLETE/ROLLED_BACK/SKIPPED/STALE/DISMISSED + mode-gated
   Sort: Severity DESC → Impact DESC → Effort ASC
   Tiebreak: most unblocks → Sec/QA over polish → core flow → smallest blast radius → oldest
   Stale items (>2 cycles) → revalidate before selecting

5. EXECUTE DOE
   Git: verify clean tree. Create atomic commit after success.
   Directive → Orchestration → Blast Radius → Execution
   DRY RUN → predicted diff, STOP

6. VERIFY (tiered)
   Tier 1 Static: type-check + lint + blast radius imports (every item)
   Tier 2 Unit: +unit tests (business logic/utils/state changes)
   Tier 3 Build: +full build (config/deps/shared module changes)
   Tier 4 E2E: +targeted E2E spec (route/page/form/nav changes)
   E2E: run only relevant spec. Missing spec → QA backlog item, not blocking.
   Auto-fix: 1 retry on deterministic failures. Second fail → STOP.
   UX Beautify items: Tier 1 only (no unit tests for visual changes).
   Generated asset scripts (scripts/generate-assets.ts): verify script exits 0
   and output files exist in public/assets/generated/ before committing.

7. UPDATE STATE
   Git commit: "[Governor] BL-XXX: <summary>"
   Changelog + status + scores + rollback + unblock dependents
   Update efficiency metrics
   UX Beautify: record BEFORE/AFTER UX Clarity + Beautify Quality scores.
   Record asset manifest in changelog (list of generated files).

8. RE-AUDIT impacted files (relevant specialists only)
   Regression → ROLLBACK

9. LOOP OR STOP
   Checkpoint threshold reached → pause, await user
```

---

## RESUME PROTOCOL

On Step 1, check for IN_PROGRESS items:
- **Files match expected "after"** → change was written. Run verification. Pass → complete. Fail → rollback.
- **Files match expected "before"** → change was not written. Reset to OPEN, re-enter at Step 4.
- **Files match neither** → STOP. Inconsistent state. Ask user.
- **Multiple IN_PROGRESS** → STOP. State corruption.
- **IN_PROGRESS Beautify item + partial generated assets** → check asset manifest. Missing files → re-run generation script. If script not present → STOP, ask user.

