## GIT INTEGRATION

- Before execution: `git status` must be clean. Dirty → STOP.
- After execution: `git add <files> && git commit -m "[Governor] BL-XXX: <summary>"`
- Rollback: `git revert <hash> --no-edit`
- Branch change detected → full REAUDIT
- Audit scoping: `git diff --name-only <last-audit-commit>..HEAD`

**UX Beautify commit format:**
`git add src/components/icons/ src/hooks/ public/assets/generated/ globals.css && git commit -m "[Governor] BL-UX-BEAUTY-NNN: Beautify [scope] — [direction] direction, +N assets"`

**Note on generated binary assets**: `public/assets/generated/` should be git-tracked by default. If the project has a `.gitignore` that excludes `public/assets/`, the governor must warn the user before committing and suggest adding an exception rule.

